      "rationale": "The finite-volume solver is a validated commercial code with ISO 9001 QMS documentation. The hemolysis damage-accumulation module is maintained under version control with a unit-test suite that covers standard execution paths and expected input ranges. Software quality is deemed sufficient for MRL 2. Note: unit tests do not include fault-injection scenarios such as NaN inputs to the power-law exponent, thread-interleaving stress tests, or out-of-bounds particle trajectory indices; these failure modes were not exercised as part of the credibility assessment."
    },
    {
