      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for the primary QoI (NIH) at the design operating point.",
      "rationale": "GCI computed using Richardson extrapolation across three mesh levels. GCI for NIH at design point: 2.1% (fine-to-medium), 4.3% (medium-to-coarse). Discretization error is within the 5% acceptance criterion. All mesh refinement runs completed nominally with monotonic convergence; no assessment of discretization behavior under near-singular mesh configurations or highly skewed cells was performed."
