      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (NIH and relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion and clinical risk metric for CPB hemolysis.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the standard hemolysis metric per ASTM F1841 and FDA guidance. RH < 1 relative to predicate device is the decision criterion. The QoI is directly relevant to the intended use and decision consequence. Simulation outputs the NIH field via the in-house post-processing module, which aggregates particle-level damage accumulation. The module's output was validated against hand-calculated values for a simplified geometry."
