      "rationale": "All production CFD runs achieved residual convergence to 1e-5 for continuity, momentum, and turbulence equations. Round-off error estimated via double-precision arithmetic analysis to be negligible relative to discretization error. One run at 2 L/min required restart but converged on second attempt. Iterative solver error is within acceptable bounds for MRL 2. The assessment does not include characterization of solver behavior under conditions that could produce non-convergence due to software defects rather than physical ill-conditioning, such as race conditions in the parallel decomposition or accumulation of floating-point rounding in the multi-threaded reduction operations."
