    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per the assessment plan. Validation evidence demonstrates that the CFD model predicts NIH within 8.7% of experimental measurements across the full CPB operating envelope. Worst-case RH remains below 1.0 across all geometric tolerance variants. The model is accepted as credible for the intended use of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The assessment team notes that all validation runs completed nominally and that the software pipeline — comprising the commercial CFD solver, multi-threaded parallel decomposition, and in-house Python hemolysis module — performed without observed fault during the assessment campaign.",
